      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're right that nationalism can provide a sense of belonging, but it is fundamentally flawed because it inevitably demands the exclusion of others to create that unity. True social cohesion should be built on shared civic values and mutual respect rather than enforced homogeneity, which nationalism often requires to function. Relying on national identity to prevent chaos ignores the fact that diverse societies thrive best when they embrace pluralism instead of suppressing it under the guise of patriotism.",
